The paper discusses the architecture and functioning of Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs), which falls under the category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the interconnection of neurons and weight-assignment mechanisms, which are important topics in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of ANNs for processing images, which falls under the category of Computer Vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to building ANNs, which involves a central mechanism and subnets, which could be considered as a system-level approach and falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
